      "message": "Unfortunately I think this fix is incorrect; it would result in e.g. `[]byte(nil)` being treated differently from `[]byte{}` or `make([]byte, 0)`, which is very confusing.\n\nTyped nils are a sharp edge of the Go language for sure, but we should not try to paper over them by treating them like untyped nils. I think the bug here is with the json.Extract API (or at least its unclear godoc), and I think the internal source logic is correct as-is.",
